        <p>One of India's earliest tiger reserves, echoing with bird calls and jungle trails.
          <br>
          The Palamau Tiger Reserve is located in the Latehar district of Jharkhand, 
          and was one of the first nine tiger reserves established in India under Project Tiger in 1973. 
          The reserve encompasses the Betla National Park and Palamau Wildlife Sanctuary. 
        </p>
